[Kandan]
Kandan's eyebrows rose, almost disappearing beneath his fringe.
"You have an uncommonly strong sensing ability. In most malkemists
it begins and almost exclusively ends with being able to identify
their own vills."

The night after Jack arrives at the farm, otherwise known as
Pamsley, he finds a dead body. There is a lot of blood. It is
almost certainly a malkemist because anybody else would have been
covered in blood from head to toe. The masters at Pamsley suspects
the Soldier who just arrived, as he is a stranger to them. Kandan
offers that the man who died (who he knew) was quite an
accomplished malkemist, so doubts that the man could have done the
deed. Kandan tells Jack that he does not know the man, but this is
contradicted later when a malkemist comes to Pamsley who mentions
in Jack's hearing that "Kandan must have been devastated, they were
as thick as thieves; as close as two men could be."

Demic is the Grand Imaginer's son. He has unusual strength and
ability in malkemy, and he is hailed as some kind of prophesied boy
who will bring the malkemists back to the true order and cleanse
the land of umbral (shadow) malkemistsâ€”those who seek to give
technology and knowledge to humans, in defiance of the prime
doctrine of malkemy.

This story is set in the Earth's future. No calamity, simple energy
starvation. Technology devolved millenia ago when the humans
exhausted the easy energy of that time. Malkemists guard against
human ascendency. Their training involves connecting to their
higher selves and surrendering to their spiritual duality. The
doctrines of the church of malkemy are loosely transcribed, because
when a malkemist connects to his or her higher self, they receive
the same information. They know that their purpose is to maintain
balance. To ensure that humans do not destabilise the earth.

However, there is growing concern in the community of the
malkemists that this process is failing, and less and less
malkemists are truly surrendering, and are simply dogmatically
reciting the words of faith. Demic is seen as a revitalising
figure. There is much stress on him to perform his miracle;
whatever form it may take.

How do the malkemists keep rouges from passing technology on to
humans? Technology is a slow process. Wars can be fomented to halt
human progression, famines instigated.

Kandan!!

